#%PAM-1.0

# Example face-unlock (Howdy) stack for qbar-lock. Enable it by passing
#   qbar-lock --face-pam-service qbar-lock-face
# qbar-lock drives this as a separate, re-arming PAM conversation in parallel with
# the password and fingerprint (fprintd D-Bus) methods; the first to succeed unlocks.
#
# Howdy is OPTIONAL. Install it (e.g. the `howdy` AUR package) and enroll a face
# (`sudo howdy add`) first, then uncomment the line below. Left commented, this
# service simply never authenticates (face unlock stays off).
#
# auth sufficient pam_howdy.so
auth include login
account include login
